package com.example.artmart

val sculpture = Categories(1,"Sculpture",R.drawable.sculpture,"They originate as the product of the Kamba people, but more specifically, this tradition in its entirety can be traced back to a single man, as Robert Dick-Read wrote in his book Sanamu; Adventures in Search of African Art.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "The beginning of commercial carving among the Wakamba is attributed to a man named Mutisya Munge who, before World War 1, was known throughout Ukamba (Ukambani) for his excellence as a craftsman.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "Before the war his work was confined to traditional objects such as stools; but whilst serving with the armed forces away from home he began to occupy his idle hours by carving ‘pictures’ from his imagination, for his amusement.\n" +
        "\n" +
        "These ‘pictures’ or musings of Munge were his immediate surroundings during World War 1, mainly African soldiers, and members of his regiment in the British Carrier Corps.")
val paintings = Categories(2,"Paintings",R.drawable.painting,"Painting in Kenya has a rich history that dates back to the pre-colonial era. \n" +
        "The art was mainly used for communication and storytelling.\n "+
        "The paintings were done on rocks and caves and were used to depict the daily life of the people, their beliefs, and their culture. \n"+
        "With the arrival of Europeans in Kenya, painting in the formal European sense was introduced")
val drawings = Categories(3,"Drawings",R.drawable.wangarimaathai,"Drawing is a form of visual art in which an artist uses instruments to mark \n " +
        "paper or other two-dimensional surface. Drawing instruments include graphite pencils, pen and ink, various kinds of paints, \n" +
        "inked brushes, colored pencils, crayons, charcoal, chalk, pastels, erasers, markers, styluses, and metals (such as silverpoint")

val carvings = Categories(4,"Carvings",R.drawable.carving,"Drawing is a form of visual art in which an artist uses instruments to mark paper or other two-dimensional surface. \n" +
        "Drawing instruments include graphite pencils, pen and ink, various kinds of paints, inked brushes, colored pencils, crayons, charcoal, \n" +
        "chalk, pastels, erasers, markers, styluses, and metals (such as silverpoint")

val allcategories = listOf(sculpture, paintings, drawings, carvings)